# Network Proxy Configuration

When encountering network issues (timeouts, connection failures, SSL errors), use these settings:

- **HTTP/HTTPS Proxy**: `http://127.0.0.1:7890`
- **SSL Verification**: Can be disabled if needed

## npm

```bash
npm config set proxy http://127.0.0.1:7890
npm config set https-proxy http://127.0.0.1:7890
npm config set strict-ssl false
```

## curl / wget

```bash
export http_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:7890
export https_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:7890
```

## Rust (cargo)

Set environment variable `HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7890` or configure in `.cargo/config.toml`.

## Git

```bash
git config --global http.proxy http://127.0.0.1:7890
git config --global https.proxy http://127.0.0.1:7890
```
